</section>

<!-- CTF -->
<section id="ctf">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <p class="eyebrow">// competition</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">CTF &amp; Tech Challenge</h2>
    <div class="divider"></div>
    <p class="section-lead">
      An overnight Capture The Flag competition running in parallel with a Technical Challenge.
      Test your skills across multiple categories — from beginner to expert level.
    </p>
    <div class="ctf-grid">
      <div class="ctf-card">
        <div class="ctf-icon">🌐</div>
        <div class="ctf-name">Web Exploitation</div>
        <div class="ctf-desc">SQLi, XSS, SSRF, authentication bypasses, and more. Break web apps like a pro.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="ctf-card">
        <div class="ctf-icon">🔬</div>
        <div class="ctf-name">Reverse Engineering</div>
        <div class="ctf-desc">Disassemble binaries, crack obfuscated code, and uncover hidden logic.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="ctf-card">
        <div class="ctf-icon">🔐</div>
        <div class="ctf-name">Cryptography</div>
        <div class="ctf-desc">Classic ciphers, modern crypto vulnerabilities, and mathematical puzzles.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="ctf-card">
        <div class="ctf-icon">🕵️</div>
        <div class="ctf-name">OSINT</div>
        <div class="ctf-desc">Open-source intelligence gathering. Find what's hiding in plain sight.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="ctf-card">
        <div class="ctf-icon">🧬</div>
        <div class="ctf-name">Forensics</div>
        <div class="ctf-desc">Memory dumps, packet captures, steganography, and file carving.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="ctf-card">
        <div class="ctf-icon">💡</div>
        <div class="ctf-name">Technical Challenge</div>
        <div class="ctf-desc">A separate challenge track testing applied knowledge in real-world scenarios with jury evaluation.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- TRAINING -->
<section id="training">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <p class="eyebrow">// upcoming</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Training Program</h2>
    <div class="divider"></div>
    <div class="training-banner">
      <span class="icon">📡</span>
      <p>
        Following UCT, we'll launch a <strong>full training cycle on Cybersecurity Basics &amp; CTF Methodology</strong>,
        running through the summer. Open to all students across Tunisian universities.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="training-timeline">
      <div class="tl-item">
        <div class="tl-dot">01</div>
        <div class="tl-content">
          <h4>What is Cybersecurity?</h4>
          <p>Foundational concepts: CIA triad, threat actors, attack surfaces, career paths.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="tl-item">
        <div class="tl-dot">02</div>
        <div class="tl-content">
          <h4>Networking Essentials</h4>
          <p>TCP/IP, DNS, HTTP, Wireshark basics. Understanding what flows through the wire.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="tl-item">
        <div class="tl-dot">03</div>
        <div class="tl-content">
          <h4>Linux for Security</h4>
          <p>Command line mastery, file permissions, scripting for automation.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="tl-item">
        <div class="tl-dot">04</div>
        <div class="tl-content">
          <h4>Web Security Fundamentals</h4>
          <p>OWASP Top 10 hands-on — SQLi, XSS, IDOR, and practical exploitation.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="tl-item">
        <div class="tl-dot">05</div>
        <div class="tl-content">
          <h4>Intro to CTF Methodology</h4>
          <p>How to think like a CTF player: tooling, category strategies, writeup culture.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="tl-item">
        <div class="tl-dot">06</div>
        <div class="tl-content">
          <h4>Practice CTF</h4>
          <p>Internal mini-CTF to apply all skills learned throughout the training cycle.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- NETWORKING -->
<section id="networking">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <p class="eyebrow">// why attend</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">More Than a Congress</h2>
    <div class="divider"></div>
    <p class="section-lead">
      UCT is designed to be the intersection of technical depth and real career opportunity.
    </p>
    <div class="features-grid">
      <div class="feature-card">
        <div class="feature-num">// 01</div>
        <div class="feature-title">Expert Speakers</div>
        <div class="feature-desc">Prominent figures from Tunisia's cybersecurity scene. Real practitioners sharing real insights.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-card">
        <div class="feature-num">// 02</div>
        <div class="feature-title">Round Table</div>
        <div class="feature-desc">A curated panel discussion on the cyber landscape — careers, threats, and the industry's direction.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-card">
        <div class="feature-num">// 03</div>
        <div class="feature-title">Networking</div>
        <div class="feature-desc">Connect with professionals, recruiters, and peers across Tunisian universities and companies.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-card">
        <div class="feature-num">// 04</div>
        <div class="feature-title">Competitions</div>
        <div class="feature-desc">Prove your skills and win prizes in the CTF and Technical Challenge competitions.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- VENUE -->
<section id="venue">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <p class="eyebrow">// location</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Venue</h2>
    <div class="divider"></div>
    <div class="venue-grid">
      <div class="venue-map">
        <iframe
          src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d51885.09873282394!2d11.013!3d35.504!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x1302360abcfc9f01%3A0x7f9e2c2ad8dc2a79!2sMahdia%2C%20Tunisia!5e0!3m2!1sen!2stn!4v1700000000000"
          allowfullscreen="" loading="lazy">
        </iframe>
      </div>
