        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- FAQ -->
<section id="faq">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <p class="eyebrow">// help</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">FAQ</h2>
    <div class="divider"></div>
    <div class="faq-list">
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
          Who can attend UCT?
          <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-a">
          UCT is open to all university students in Tunisia, regardless of major. You don't need to be a CS student — curiosity about cybersecurity is enough. IEEE membership is encouraged but not mandatory.
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
          Is the CTF beginner-friendly?
          <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-a">
          Yes. The CTF is designed with multiple difficulty levels, from introductory challenges accessible to beginners all the way to advanced flags for experienced players. The pre-event training program also prepares you to play.
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
          What's the overnight CTF like?
          <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-a">
          The CTF runs from late Day 1 through the morning of Day 2. The venue stays open overnight with food, drinks, and power infrastructure provided. A safety and logistics checklist is prepared by the organizing team to ensure a comfortable experience.
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
          Do I need a team to participate in the CTF?
          <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-a">
          Teams are recommended (2–4 people), but you can register solo and we'll help you find teammates. Team formation details will be shared after registration.
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
          How do I become an ambassador for UCT?
          <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-a">
          UCT ambassadors represent the congress within their university or club, drive registrations, and stay connected with the organizing team. Contact us via email or social media and mention your school — we'll share the ambassador brief.
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
          What is the training program and when does it start?
          <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-a">
          After the congress, the IEEE CS Chapter ISIMA will launch a free cybersecurity &amp; CTF training series running through the summer. Sessions cover networking, Linux, web security, crypto, and more. Open to all — follow our social media for announcements.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- CONTACT -->
<section id="contact">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <p class="eyebrow">// get involved</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Contact &amp; Register</h2>
    <div class="divider"></div>
    <div class="contact-grid">
      <div>
        <p class="section-lead" style="margin-bottom:1.5rem;">
          Questions? Want to be an ambassador? Interested in sponsoring UCT?
          Reach out — we're happy to chat.
        </p>
        <div class="contact-links">
          <a class="contact-link" href="mailto:ieee.cs.isima@gmail.com">
            <span class="icon">✉</span>
            ieee.cs.isima@gmail.com
          </a>
          <a class="contact-link" href="https://www.instagram.com/ieee.uct" target="_blank">
            <span class="icon">📸</span>
            @ieee.uct
          </a>
          <a class="contact-link" href="#">
            <span class="icon">💼</span>
            IEEE CS Chapter · ISIMA Student Branch
          </a>
        </div>
        <div class="social-row">
          <a class="social-btn" href="https://www.instagram.com/ieee.uct" target="_blank">
            <span>IG</span> instagram
          </a>
          <a class="social-btn" href="#">
            <span>LI</span> linkedin
          </a>
          <a class="social-btn" href="#">
            <span>FB</span> facebook
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="register-box">
        <h3>Join UCT 2</h3>
        <p>Secure your spot at Tunisia's cybersecurity congress. Limited seats available.</p>
        <a href="mailto:ieee.cs.isima@gmail.com" class="btn-primary" style="display:inline-block;">Register Now</a>
        <p class="note">// Registration form link coming soon — follow @ieee.uct for updates</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- FOOTER -->
<footer>
  <div class="footer-logo">UCT_2 · IEEE CS · ISIMA SB</div>
  <div class="footer-copy">© 2025 IEEE CS Chapter ISIMA Student Branch. All rights reserved.</div>
</footer>

<script>
  // THEME
  const toggle = document.getElementById('themeToggle');
  toggle.addEventListener('click', () => {
    const html = document.documentElement;
    const isDark = html.getAttribute('data-theme') === 'dark';
    html.setAttribute('data-theme', isDark ? 'light' : 'dark');
    toggle.textContent = isDark ? '[ DARK ]' : '[ LIGHT ]';
  });

  // HAMBURGER
  const ham = document.getElementById('hamburger');
  const mob = document.getElementById('mobileMenu');
  ham.addEventListener('click', () => mob.classList.toggle('open'));
  function closeMobile() { mob.classList.remove('open'); }

  // DAY TABS
  function switchDay(n) {
    document.querySelectorAll('.schedule-block').forEach(b => b.classList.remove('active'));
    document.querySelectorAll('.day-tab').forEach(t => t.classList.remove('active'));
    document.getElementById('day' + n).classList.add('active');
    document.querySelectorAll('.day-tab')[n - 1].classList.add('active');
  }

  // FAQ
  function toggleFaq(btn) {
    const item = btn.closest('.faq-item');
    const isOpen = item.classList.contains('open');
    document.querySelectorAll('.faq-item').forEach(i => i.classList.remove('open'));
    if (!isOpen) item.classList.add('open');
  }

  // COUNTDOWN — target: Sep 26 2025 09:00
  const target = new Date('2025-09-26T09:00:00').getTime();
  function updateCountdown() {
    const now = Date.now();
    const diff = target - now;
    if (diff <= 0) {
      document.getElementById('cd-days').textContent = '00';
      document.getElementById('cd-hours').textContent = '00';
      document.getElementById('cd-mins').textContent = '00';
      document.getElementById('cd-secs').textContent = '00';
      return;
    }
    const d = Math.floor(diff / 86400000);
    const h = Math.floor((diff % 86400000) / 3600000);
    const m = Math.floor((diff % 3600000) / 60000);
    const s = Math.floor((diff % 60000) / 1000);
    document.getElementById('cd-days').textContent  = String(d).padStart(2,'0');
    document.getElementById('cd-hours').textContent = String(h).padStart(2,'0');
    document.getElementById('cd-mins').textContent  = String(m).padStart(2,'0');
    document.getElementById('cd-secs').textContent  = String(s).padStart(2,'0');
  }
  updateCountdown();
  setInterval(updateCountdown, 1000);
</script>
</body>
</html>
